nodes.name: secureValueErrorData
nodes.description: Represents an issue in one of the data fields that was provided by the user. The error is considered resolved when the field's value changes.

nodes.name: secureValueErrorFrontSide
nodes.description: Represents an issue with the front side of a document. The error is considered resolved when the file with the front side of the document changes.

nodes.name: secureValueErrorReverseSide
nodes.description: Represents an issue with the reverse side of a document. The error is considered resolved when the file with reverse side of the document changes.

nodes.name: secureValueErrorSelfie
nodes.description: Represents an issue with the selfie with a document. The error is considered resolved when the file with the selfie changes.

nodes.name: secureValueErrorFile
nodes.description: Represents an issue with a document scan. The error is considered resolved when the file with the document scan changes.

nodes.name: secureValueErrorFiles
nodes.description: Represents an issue with a list of scans. The error is considered resolved when the list of files containing the scans changes.

nodes.name: secureValueErrorTranslationFile
nodes.description: Represents an issue with one of the files that constitute the translation of a document. The error is considered resolved when the file changes.

nodes.name: secureValueErrorTranslationFiles
nodes.description: Represents an issue with the translated version of a document. The error is considered resolved when a file with the document translation changes.

nodes.name: users.setSecureValueErrors
nodes.description: Notify the user that the sent passport data contains some errors The user will not be able to re-submit their Passport data to you until the errors are fixed (the contents of the field for which you returned the error must change).
